# Icon Usage Guidelines

## **Always Use Lucide React Icons**

- **DO:** Import and use Lucide React icons for all visual elements
- **DON'T:** Use emojis, Unicode symbols, or other icon libraries

## **Icon Import Pattern**

```typescript
// ✅ DO: Import specific icons from lucide-react
import { Target, Music, Mic, Play, Pause, Settings } from "lucide-react";

// ❌ DON'T: Use emojis or Unicode symbols
<span>🎯</span>
<span>🎵</span>
<span>🗣️</span>
```

## **Icon Usage Examples**

```typescript
// ✅ DO: Use Lucide icons with proper sizing and styling
<div className="w-8 h-8 bg-primary/10 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center">
  <Target className="w-4 h-4 text-primary" />
</div>

// ✅ DO: Use icons in buttons and interactive elements
<Button>
  <Play className="w-4 h-4 mr-2" />
  클래스 시작
</Button>

// ❌ DON'T: Use emojis in UI components
<div className="w-8 h-8 bg-primary/10 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center">
  <span className="text-primary text-sm">🎯</span>
</div>
```

## **Common Icon Mappings**

| Purpose | Lucide Icon | Usage |
|---------|-------------|-------|
| Target/Goal | `Target` | Personalization, goals |
| Music/Audio | `Music` | Music synchronization |
| Voice/Speech | `Mic` | AI voice coaching |
| Play | `Play` | Start class, play video |
| Pause | `Pause` | Pause class, pause video |
| Settings | `Settings` | User preferences |
| User/Profile | `User` | User account |
| Heart/Like | `Heart` | Favorites, likes |
| Star/Rating | `Star` | Ratings, favorites |
| Search | `Search` | Search functionality |
| Menu | `Menu` | Navigation menu |
| Home | `Home` | Home page |
| Calendar | `Calendar` | Schedule, dates |
| Clock | `Clock` | Time, duration |

## **Icon Sizing Guidelines**

```typescript
// Small icons (16px) - inline with text
<Settings className="w-4 h-4" />

// Medium icons (20px) - buttons and cards
<Target className="w-5 h-5" />

// Large icons (24px) - prominent features
<Music className="w-6 h-6" />

// Extra large icons (32px) - hero sections
<Play className="w-8 h-8" />
```

